WEBVTT

00:00.935 --> 00:02.467
[ school bell rings ]

00:02.469 --> 00:05.170
As the official party planner
for your birthday --

00:06.073 --> 00:08.406
Mmm. Well, I've taken
the liberty

00:08.408 --> 00:10.875
Of putting together
some potential themes.

00:11.011 --> 00:12.611
We could do glam rock...

00:12.746 --> 00:14.279
Super mario brothers...

00:14.414 --> 00:16.348
The roaring twenties.

00:16.483 --> 00:19.684
[ speaking japanese ]

00:19.820 --> 00:22.154
Clams. Clams!

00:22.289 --> 00:24.156
What? Where?
On me?

00:24.291 --> 00:27.225
Langley's getting...
An awww shucks.

00:27.361 --> 00:30.495
What's that?
Awww shucks
is a fast food chain

00:30.497 --> 00:33.098
With the best fried clams
in the world,

00:33.233 --> 00:36.035
And they're served
in their own shell!

00:40.240 --> 00:42.040
Ohh, and they have
this sauce --

00:42.042 --> 00:43.708
Special sauce!

00:43.844 --> 00:47.579
It's so beloved people have
literally been buried with it.

00:47.714 --> 00:49.581
And we're talking
living people,

00:49.716 --> 00:53.318
People who just want to be alone
in the dirt with the sauce.

00:53.453 --> 00:55.120
Well, if my best friends
love it,

00:55.255 --> 00:56.455
I'm sure
I'll love it too!

00:56.590 --> 00:59.124
When do I get to slurp up
my first clam?

00:59.259 --> 01:01.126
Sorry, gross,
knew it as soon as I said it.

01:01.261 --> 01:03.127
The grand opening
is tomorrow.

01:03.129 --> 01:04.462
Hey, what's that?

01:04.464 --> 01:06.531
I'm planning toshi's
birthday party.

01:06.667 --> 01:08.933
Is he still calling it
his "quinceañera"?

01:09.069 --> 01:13.172
Yes, and I don't know how to
ask why without sounding racist.

01:15.942 --> 01:18.010
♪ good morning, u.S.A. ♪

01:18.144 --> 01:21.946
♪ I got a feelin' that
it's gonna be a wonderful day ♪

01:21.948 --> 01:24.949
♪ the sun in the sky
has a smile on his face ♪

01:25.085 --> 01:29.621
♪ and he's shinin' a salute
to the american race ♪

01:31.425 --> 01:34.626
♪ oh, boy, it's swell to say ♪

01:34.761 --> 01:37.529
♪ good -- ♪
♪ good morning, u.S.A. ♪

01:37.531 --> 01:38.497
Aah!

01:39.900 --> 01:43.202
♪ good morning, u.S.A. ♪

01:45.439 --> 01:47.372
These clams
must be amazing.

01:47.507 --> 01:49.508
Is that bruce springsteen
in line?

01:49.643 --> 01:52.377
Yeah, the boss
is a huge shucker.

01:52.379 --> 01:53.778
And watch this.

01:53.780 --> 01:56.515
Shucks for you!
Shucks for me!

01:56.650 --> 01:59.651
All: ♪ at awww shucks
we're all clam-I-ly! ♪

01:59.786 --> 02:02.254
Taking a selfie
with the secret sauce tank

02:02.389 --> 02:04.456
Is another
rite of passage.

02:04.591 --> 02:06.258
[ camera shutter clicks ]

02:06.393 --> 02:09.928
And the tank is actually full
of real sauce!

02:09.930 --> 02:12.130
Look!
Excuse me, sir!

02:12.132 --> 02:13.665
Please keep away
from the sauce tank!

02:13.800 --> 02:16.468
It's a violation
of rule number 47-b!

02:16.603 --> 02:19.871
Customers are only allowed
one sauce squirt per clam!

02:20.006 --> 02:21.073
I don't like you.

02:21.208 --> 02:23.875
Um, sir.
Who are you?

02:24.010 --> 02:25.343
The name's matt m.

02:25.345 --> 02:26.745
Another matt
works here, too.

02:26.747 --> 02:29.281
Assistant manager
of store number 52.

02:29.416 --> 02:32.817
Shucks is my religion,
the employee manual is my bible,

02:32.819 --> 02:34.419
And this is my sermon...

02:34.421 --> 02:38.090
One sauce squirt per clam,
my son!

02:38.224 --> 02:40.559
[ indistinct conversations ]

02:40.694 --> 02:43.095
You guys are the experts.
What should I get?

02:43.229 --> 02:44.629
There's a secret
menu too.

02:44.765 --> 02:47.766
Seaweed style,
barnacle style,

02:47.901 --> 02:50.435
And if you say,
"clam me," they...

02:50.570 --> 02:52.171
Woman: Clam me!

02:53.239 --> 02:54.773
[ mouth full ]
thank you!

02:54.775 --> 02:59.678
You need to take your very
first bite on the clam throne!

03:03.784 --> 03:04.849
Well...?

03:04.851 --> 03:06.485
Yeah...

03:07.721 --> 03:09.488
...They're...

03:10.724 --> 03:11.857
...Fine.

03:14.060 --> 03:17.261
I mean, they're fine...Ally
in my mouth

03:17.263 --> 03:19.197
And I couldn't
be happier?

03:19.199 --> 03:21.266
[ people grumbling ]

03:21.401 --> 03:23.602
Heads up,
clamboni coming through!

03:23.737 --> 03:25.537
What the hell
is going on?

03:25.672 --> 03:28.273
This is the coldest reception
the clamboni has ever gotten!

03:28.408 --> 03:30.809
And I've driven this thing
into a church!

03:35.991 --> 03:37.056
Mail's here!

03:37.192 --> 03:38.791
That's mr. Miner's mail.

03:38.926 --> 03:40.193
Who...

03:40.328 --> 03:41.861
Is mr. Miner?

03:41.863 --> 03:43.596
The guy who lived here
before us.

03:43.731 --> 03:45.665
We've been getting his mail
ever since we moved in.

03:45.667 --> 03:47.266
Why don't you just
throw it away?

03:47.402 --> 03:49.802
And commit
a federal crime?

03:49.937 --> 03:52.538
I have two strikes
and I'm saving the third

03:52.674 --> 03:55.008
For when the king tut exhibit
comes back to town!

03:55.143 --> 03:57.877
You should find mr. Miner
and give him his mail.

03:57.879 --> 03:59.278
He probably misses it.

03:59.414 --> 04:00.880
[ sarcastically ]
oh, "find him"? No sweat.

04:01.016 --> 04:03.883
I'll just run his mail
through a cia profiling machine

04:03.885 --> 04:06.619
And create a detailed profile
we can track.

04:06.754 --> 04:09.422
Wait, what if I run his mail
through a cia profiling machine

04:09.557 --> 04:11.757
And create a detailed profile
we can track?!

04:11.759 --> 04:12.692
Could that work?

04:12.827 --> 04:14.360
Jeff, I wouldn't
have said it twice

04:14.495 --> 04:16.095
If I didn't think
it could work.

04:16.097 --> 04:18.497
[ school bell rings ]

04:18.499 --> 04:20.900
[ indistinct conversations ]

04:20.902 --> 04:22.702
Great, it's spreading.

04:22.704 --> 04:25.571
Steve, you gotta give shucks
another chance!

04:25.707 --> 04:27.306
You must've had
a bad bite.

04:27.442 --> 04:30.276
We made you
a better bite.

04:36.184 --> 04:38.651
Yum yummity
yum yum yummers!

04:38.786 --> 04:39.785
Alright!

04:39.921 --> 04:42.422
There's a shucker
born every minute.

04:44.191 --> 04:45.658
Blech!

04:46.394 --> 04:56.269
♪♪

04:56.404 --> 05:00.940
♪♪

05:01.076 --> 05:02.341
[ whistle blows ]

05:02.343 --> 05:09.348
♪♪

05:09.484 --> 05:12.217
[ insects buzzing ]

05:12.219 --> 05:18.557
♪♪

05:18.559 --> 05:19.759
[ blade clinks ]

05:19.761 --> 05:23.897
♪♪

05:24.031 --> 05:25.899
[ clapping ]

05:26.033 --> 05:29.435
♪♪

05:29.570 --> 05:32.305
Fee-fi-fo-fum,

05:32.440 --> 05:35.641
I smell something nasty
in locker 211.

05:35.643 --> 05:37.343
Open her up, chappy!

05:40.982 --> 05:43.716
Fine, I'll admit it!
I don't like shucks!

05:43.851 --> 05:45.518
Do what you must!
Tar and feather me!

05:45.653 --> 05:47.252
Put my head and hands

05:47.254 --> 05:48.721
Through whatever you call
that big wooden thing!

05:48.856 --> 05:52.391
It's okay that clams
aren't your jam, buddy.

05:52.527 --> 05:54.393
If you don't like 'em,
don't eat 'em.

05:54.529 --> 05:56.261
Really?
That's great.

05:56.263 --> 05:58.464
I was worried you guys
were gonna exclude me

05:58.466 --> 06:00.065
Or -- or shun me or...

06:00.067 --> 06:03.268
I believe the word you're
looking for is "ostracize."

06:03.270 --> 06:07.840
And "that big wooden thing"
is called a "pillory."

06:10.145 --> 06:14.347
And now the machine will make
a visual profile of mr. Miner

06:14.482 --> 06:16.282
Based on the data
from his mail.

06:16.417 --> 06:18.083
[ beeping ]

06:18.085 --> 06:20.286
Francine:
So miner is super jacked?

06:20.421 --> 06:21.620
Well, he does subscribe

06:21.622 --> 06:23.623
To<i> muscle madness</i>
fitness magazine.

06:23.758 --> 06:25.558
And the hawaiian shirt?

06:25.693 --> 06:27.960
That's either his
jimmy buffet fan club membership

06:28.095 --> 06:29.895
Or his coupons
from trader joe's.

06:29.897 --> 06:33.432
Okay. Then how do you explain
the big pirate hat?

06:33.568 --> 06:35.701
The library keeps sending him
overdue book notices

06:35.703 --> 06:36.969
For "treasure island."

06:37.104 --> 06:39.839
So how do we find
this junk mail hunk?

06:39.974 --> 06:42.708
The tracking machine's
compiling his profile data

06:42.710 --> 06:44.577
And now we print
the results.

06:44.712 --> 06:47.981
Whoops, I just sent it
to the 3-d printer by mistake.

06:49.784 --> 06:52.918
The cia
has a 3-d printer?

06:53.054 --> 06:54.720
Yeah. We also have
a coffee maker.

06:54.722 --> 06:56.489
Does that
blow you away?

06:58.793 --> 07:00.926
So what's the theme
of this party?

07:01.062 --> 07:02.595
Lame bullshit
nobody likes?

07:02.730 --> 07:04.797
It's classic literature
come to life!

07:04.932 --> 07:07.400
There's an "of mice and men"
rabbit-petting room,

07:07.535 --> 07:09.068
A "scarlet letter" room

07:09.070 --> 07:11.470
Where we all shame toshi
as an adulteress,

07:11.606 --> 07:13.138
And a room full of monitors

07:13.140 --> 07:15.941
Where we can watch all
the other rooms like "1984"!

07:16.077 --> 07:17.210
No batman room?

07:17.344 --> 07:18.544
Literature, klaus.

07:18.679 --> 07:21.080
Comic books
are books, steve!

07:21.216 --> 07:23.549
[ doorbell rings ]

07:23.551 --> 07:25.418
Happy birthday,
toshi!

07:25.553 --> 07:27.086
Step into this house

07:27.222 --> 07:30.490
And step into the
required reading of our grade!

07:33.895 --> 07:36.562
I won't spoil all the surprises,
but the big finale

07:36.697 --> 07:38.964
Is we all take a hot-air balloon
ride together

07:38.966 --> 07:41.834
Like "around the world
in eighty days"!

07:41.969 --> 07:44.770
Oh, no,
my grandma just died.

07:44.772 --> 07:46.505
Oh, gosh,
that's terrible!

07:46.507 --> 07:48.908
I need to go
plan her funeral!

07:48.910 --> 07:51.844
Holy cow!
My grandma died, too.

07:51.979 --> 07:54.179
She was in a duel
with barry's grandma

07:54.181 --> 07:57.382
And they shot each other
at the same time!

07:57.384 --> 07:58.518
Wait, what?

08:02.189 --> 08:03.322
I don't get it, klaus.

08:03.458 --> 08:04.457
What happened?

08:04.592 --> 08:06.993
Of course.

08:11.799 --> 08:14.600
Crowd: Happy birthday!

08:14.602 --> 08:17.403
[ cheering ]

08:17.538 --> 08:19.405
They had their own party...

08:19.540 --> 08:20.673
And didn't invite me?

08:20.808 --> 08:22.942
Billy went
to a party...

08:23.077 --> 08:24.944
And lied about it?

08:25.079 --> 08:27.746
He told me he couldn't
go grave-robbing

08:27.748 --> 08:31.584
Because he had to study
for a spanish quiz!

08:35.965 --> 08:39.700
Can't believe my stupid friends
ditched me for stupid clams.

08:39.702 --> 08:41.301
I hate awww shucks!

08:41.303 --> 08:42.770
Hohoho, steve.

08:42.905 --> 08:45.439
I'm loving this dark turn
you're taking.

08:45.575 --> 08:47.775
You're giving off
major joker vibes,

08:47.910 --> 08:49.443
The joaquin phoenix
version.

08:49.579 --> 08:51.178
Cast out from society

08:51.313 --> 08:54.148
For not absolutely
loving clams.

08:56.118 --> 08:58.919
Couldn't help but overhear.
I hate shucks, too.

08:58.921 --> 09:00.520
When they opened
next to sub hub,

09:00.522 --> 09:03.391
Parking got so bad I have to
skate 25 minutes to work!

09:03.526 --> 09:06.193
You skateboard?
Please, I've been
shredding the gnar

09:06.328 --> 09:08.328
Since tony hawk
was tony egg.

09:08.330 --> 09:11.198
Why can't my friends see
how terrible that place is?!

09:11.333 --> 09:13.934
Look, all restaurants
are secretly gross.

09:14.070 --> 09:16.070
At sub hub we call it
"shaved turkey"

09:16.205 --> 09:19.339
Because we scrape mold off
each morning with a razor blade.

09:19.475 --> 09:23.778
You wanna take down shucks,
get a job there and dig up dirt.

09:25.948 --> 09:28.983
I'm gonna say it --
radical!

09:30.352 --> 09:34.288
This 3d-printed mr. Miner
looks hot as hell,

09:34.290 --> 09:36.891
But we're no closer
to getting rid of his mail.

09:37.026 --> 09:38.726
Huh.
He's got a switch.

09:39.762 --> 09:41.161
<i> Hello,</i>
<i> current occupant.</i>

09:41.163 --> 09:43.764
<i> We'll pay cash</i>
<i> to buy your home!</i>

09:43.899 --> 09:45.833
Surprisingly
sexy voice.

09:45.968 --> 09:48.035
<i> Dear virginia gas & electric</i>
<i> customer.</i>

09:48.170 --> 09:52.306
<i> Installing solar panels can</i>
<i>save you hundreds on your bill!</i>

09:52.308 --> 09:55.709
Wait, he's just saying nonsense
like a hot dummy.

09:55.711 --> 09:57.978
Actually,
it's yes-sense.

09:58.114 --> 10:01.515
He's saying "hello" but he
only knows words from his mail.

10:01.517 --> 10:03.517
<i> You're pre-approved already!</i>

10:03.653 --> 10:05.519
See, he's telling me
I'm right!

10:05.521 --> 10:09.189
If this guy knows all the info
in mr. Miner's mail,

10:09.191 --> 10:11.325
We can use him
to find the real miner!

10:11.327 --> 10:14.128
Oh, good, stan.
We haven't seen you in weeks.

10:14.263 --> 10:16.130
You're supposed to be
overseeing the drone strike

10:16.265 --> 10:18.065
On that afghan
terrorist bunker.

10:18.200 --> 10:20.868
Yeah, well, I'm doing this
instead, okay?

10:22.338 --> 10:25.539
This is a clam.
God's little miracle.

10:25.675 --> 10:27.274
It's hard as hell
on the outside,

10:27.409 --> 10:30.210
But that's why it's so
gosh dang tender on the inside.

10:30.212 --> 10:33.213
Now, the secret
to shucking clams is -- ow!

10:33.215 --> 10:34.615
The secret is -- ow!

10:34.750 --> 10:36.884
The secret --
ow! Ow-ow-ow-ow!

10:37.019 --> 10:38.418
Just give me
the damn knife!

10:38.420 --> 10:40.888
Taking the initiative,
I like that.

10:42.825 --> 10:46.494
Time to dig up some dirt
and bring this place down!

10:46.629 --> 10:53.501
♪♪

10:53.636 --> 10:55.703
Aha!
Rat droppings!

10:55.838 --> 10:57.771
A major
health code violation!

10:57.907 --> 10:59.307
[ sniffs ] damn it.

10:59.441 --> 11:01.842
These are droppings
from the super-fresh clams!

11:01.977 --> 11:03.177
If there's one thing
I know,

11:03.312 --> 11:04.979
It's the smell
of underwater poops.

11:05.114 --> 11:06.981
Maybe there's nothing wrong
with their food,

11:07.116 --> 11:10.851
But every fast food chain
screws over their employees.

11:13.189 --> 11:16.990
Whoa, shucks workers get
a month of paid vacation!

11:16.992 --> 11:18.926
And their retirement plan
is a 402(k),

11:19.061 --> 11:20.994
One better than usual!

11:20.996 --> 11:22.796
There's no dirt
anywhere!

11:22.798 --> 11:25.399
Maybe this place is perfect,
and<i> I'm</i> the problem.

11:25.535 --> 11:28.468
Maybe my friends are right.
What's wrong with me?!

11:28.470 --> 11:30.337
There's nothing wrong
with you, steve.

11:30.472 --> 11:31.739
It's society!

11:31.874 --> 11:33.207
You're a terrific kid.

11:33.342 --> 11:35.876
You should just
poison the clams.

11:36.011 --> 11:37.811
That's what the joker
would do --

11:37.813 --> 11:40.013
Shut up about the joker,
klaus! Yow!

11:40.015 --> 11:42.015
Roger: Uh-oh!
I know that sound!

11:42.017 --> 11:43.617
Minor flesh wound.

11:43.753 --> 11:46.153
Manual says you got 10 minutes
to clean it and cream it.

11:46.288 --> 11:49.056
First-aid kit's in my office.
Clock starts now!

11:50.092 --> 11:52.560
Stop looking for
the first-aid kit, klaus.

11:52.694 --> 11:54.161
I want it to get infected,

11:54.296 --> 11:57.231
Like society has been infected
by these clam-lovers!

11:57.233 --> 11:59.299
Again, loving the darkness,
steve.

11:59.435 --> 12:03.237
And if we're looking for dirt,
I think we're getting warmer.

12:06.175 --> 12:09.577
It's a keypad lock,
and we don't know the password.

12:09.712 --> 12:11.245
Unless...
[ beeping ]

12:11.247 --> 12:12.780
Yup, the password is "clams."

12:12.915 --> 12:14.382
Of course the password
is "clams."

12:18.520 --> 12:20.588
Attention, shuckers!

12:20.722 --> 12:24.524
I've learned information
I feel obligated to share.

12:24.526 --> 12:28.996
Turns out the "special sauce"
you all love sooooo much...

12:29.131 --> 12:31.398
Is just mayo
and tartar sauce!

12:31.533 --> 12:36.604
Leave it to shucks to make
the ordinary extraordinary!

12:36.738 --> 12:38.071
[ cheering ]

12:38.073 --> 12:40.340
[ laughing ]
am I the only one

12:40.476 --> 12:42.943
Who hasn't been brainwashed
by this place?!

12:43.078 --> 12:45.012
I feel like
I'm going insane!

12:45.147 --> 12:47.615
Yes! That's total
joker talk!

12:47.750 --> 12:50.618
I'm not
the freakin' joker!

12:50.752 --> 12:51.751
Steve?!

12:51.753 --> 12:52.820
[ bubbling ]

12:52.955 --> 12:54.822
[ suspenseful music plays ]

12:58.828 --> 13:00.894
[ gasps ]
joker, joker, joker!

13:00.896 --> 13:04.564
Haha-haha-hahahaha!

13:04.700 --> 13:06.634
[ laughing ]

13:06.768 --> 13:08.302
Stop him!

13:08.437 --> 13:10.704
That much exposure to the toxic
preservative in special sauce

13:10.840 --> 13:12.106
Will drive him insane!

13:12.241 --> 13:14.508
My special sauce
is toxic?

13:14.644 --> 13:16.176
Just a smidge,

13:16.312 --> 13:18.779
But it's neutralized
by a natural chemical in clams.

13:18.914 --> 13:19.980
Is he
going to be okay?

13:19.982 --> 13:21.181
Oh, yeah, yeah, sure.

13:21.317 --> 13:22.850
After that much
sauce exposure,

13:22.985 --> 13:25.052
He just needs to eat
a hundred pounds of clams

13:25.187 --> 13:27.921
In the next 24 hours
or he'll go insane forever.

13:28.057 --> 13:30.458
That shouldn't be a problem.
He likes clams, right?

13:33.329 --> 13:35.729
Alright, 3d-printed
mr. Miner,

13:35.731 --> 13:37.331
Tell us where
real mr. Miner lives

13:37.466 --> 13:39.266
So we can dump off
all this damn mail.

13:39.401 --> 13:43.137
<i> Voter registration address</i>
<i> for mr. A. Miner --</i>

13:43.272 --> 13:44.938
<i> 416 cherry street.</i>

13:45.074 --> 13:46.340
I know where that is!

13:46.342 --> 13:47.875
Yeah,
that's<i> our</i> house, jeff.

13:48.010 --> 13:49.409
That's where his mail's
been going.

13:49.545 --> 13:52.746
He's gotta be getting these
huge muscles from somewhere.

13:52.748 --> 13:54.214
Maybe he goes to a gym?

13:54.350 --> 13:55.949
<i> Credit card</i>
<i> transaction --</i>

13:55.951 --> 13:58.352
<i> June 5th,</i>
<i> chimdale fitness club.</i>

13:58.487 --> 14:00.287
He lives in chimdale!

14:00.422 --> 14:03.157
Nobody drives to that craphole
just to use a gym.

14:03.292 --> 14:05.893
Mr. Miner,
what kind of car do you drive?

14:06.028 --> 14:08.161
<i> It's time</i>
<i> to renew auto insurance</i>

14:08.163 --> 14:11.832
<i> On your yellow</i>
<i> 2005 nissan rogue.</i>

14:11.967 --> 14:13.834
We got him.
Let's roll.

14:13.969 --> 14:17.637
Mmmmmmmmmmmmmmm.

14:17.639 --> 14:19.006
[ knock on door ]

14:21.844 --> 14:23.344
What the heck?

14:24.380 --> 14:25.946
[ groans ]

14:28.050 --> 14:30.851
[<i> laughing</i> ]

14:30.986 --> 14:32.986
<i> Good morning,</i>
<i> boys and girls!</i>

14:32.988 --> 14:35.389
<i> Your teacher's indisposed,</i>

14:35.391 --> 14:39.193
<i> So your substitute's here</i>
<i> to teach you a little lesson.</i>

14:39.328 --> 14:41.128
<i> Snot, barry, toshi,</i>

14:41.263 --> 14:45.132
<i> Please remove the items</i>
<i> I've taped under your desks.</i>

14:45.267 --> 14:47.434
[<i> laughing</i> ]

14:50.005 --> 14:53.607
<i> Now if I may direct</i>
<i> your attention out the window,</i>

14:53.609 --> 14:55.275
<i> You'll see your beloved</i>

14:55.277 --> 14:57.545
<i> Awww shucks</i>
<i> eating establishment.</i>

14:57.679 --> 15:01.081
<i> And you'll notice two</i>
<i> hot-air balloons above it.</i>

15:01.216 --> 15:02.550
Barry:
Neat! Balloons!

15:02.684 --> 15:06.820
<i> Not just balloons,</i>
<i> barry, a dilemma!</i>

15:06.822 --> 15:09.289
Neat!
Dilemma balloons!

15:09.291 --> 15:10.958
<i> The basket of one balloon</i>

15:11.093 --> 15:13.360
<i> Is filled with</i>
<i> every single clam</i>

15:13.495 --> 15:15.896
<i> From the shucks kitchen below.</i>

15:16.031 --> 15:20.300
<i> And in the other balloon</i>
<i>are all three of your grandmas,</i>

15:20.302 --> 15:23.570
<i> Who turned out to be</i>
<i> miraculously alive.</i>

15:23.705 --> 15:25.639
<i> And, uh-oh,</i>

15:25.775 --> 15:29.709
<i> I know all about</i>
<i>toshi's little clam party, too.</i>

15:29.845 --> 15:30.778
Steve,
we can explain --

15:30.912 --> 15:32.379
<i> I'll do the explaining.</i>

15:32.514 --> 15:36.116
<i> The remote control</i>
<i> has a "save clams" button</i>

15:36.251 --> 15:40.053
<i> And a -- hoo-hoo --</i>
<i> "save grams" button.</i>

15:40.189 --> 15:42.656
<i> You can only press one,</i>
<i> and when you do,</i>

15:42.658 --> 15:47.595
<i> The other balloon will be cut</i>
<i> loose and float away forever.</i>

15:47.729 --> 15:49.129
[<i> laughing</i> ]

15:49.264 --> 15:52.399
The grandmas are old!
The clams are young!

15:52.534 --> 15:54.334
The choice is clear!

15:54.336 --> 15:56.403
If god wanted us
to save grandmas,

15:56.538 --> 15:58.973
He wouldn't have
given us clams!

16:00.275 --> 16:02.075
Why so serious,
boys?

16:02.211 --> 16:04.011
Worried your little friends
will turn on you

16:04.146 --> 16:05.879
If you don't choose
the clams?

16:06.015 --> 16:08.816
Well, welcome
to my world!

16:08.951 --> 16:10.617
Awesome!

16:10.752 --> 16:13.487
I thought you'd be more
of a jack nicholson joker,

16:13.489 --> 16:15.689
But this whole twisted
moral dilemma thing

16:15.691 --> 16:17.624
Is very heath ledger!

16:17.759 --> 16:21.161
Steve, buddy.
The sauce is making you crazy!

16:21.296 --> 16:26.166
Uh uh uh, pick a balloon
or I let both go.

16:26.301 --> 16:28.368
Together:
Clams! Clams! Clams! Clams!

16:28.504 --> 16:31.438
Toshi, you know I hate
to go against a chant, but...

16:31.573 --> 16:33.040
Save the grandmas.

16:33.175 --> 16:34.275
[ beep ]

16:35.978 --> 16:37.244
[ all gasp ]

16:37.379 --> 16:38.578
Aww.

16:38.714 --> 16:41.649
Say bye-bye to your
precious mollusks, kiddies!

16:41.783 --> 16:44.784
And you have snot,
barry, and toshi to blame!

16:44.920 --> 16:46.453
The scary clown's right.

16:46.588 --> 16:49.589
They ruined
everything!

16:49.725 --> 16:53.460
Well, look at that.
Your friends walked out on you.

16:53.595 --> 16:57.931
You might even say you've
been...Ex-clam-unicated!

16:58.067 --> 17:00.234
[ geese honking ]
oh, no! Look!

17:01.803 --> 17:03.270
[ people screaming ]

17:03.405 --> 17:06.606
What's wrong?
Never seen a clam bake before?

17:06.608 --> 17:09.543
The flavor
is explosive!

17:11.681 --> 17:13.280
Great timing!

17:13.415 --> 17:15.449
[ sighs ]
this is fun.

17:18.120 --> 17:19.920
♪ I killed shucks, hey ♪

17:20.055 --> 17:21.654
♪ I'm dancing on its grave ♪

17:21.790 --> 17:25.592
[ sobbing ]
look what you've done.

17:25.594 --> 17:27.794
No, it can't be!

17:27.796 --> 17:31.864
Clamboni, noooo!

17:31.866 --> 17:34.267
Steve, we're sorry.

17:34.269 --> 17:37.003
Nobody at school
will talk to us anymore.

17:37.005 --> 17:39.139
Oh, they
"clammed up" on you

17:39.274 --> 17:41.207
Because you were
being "shellfish?"

17:41.209 --> 17:43.343
We're glad
you burned it down!

17:43.478 --> 17:46.146
In fact, we think
you should burn them all down.

17:46.281 --> 17:47.880
With our help.

17:47.882 --> 17:50.483
Burn down<i> every</i> shucks...

17:50.619 --> 17:51.752
I love it!

17:51.887 --> 17:54.687
Only question is
where to start.

17:54.689 --> 17:57.490
We start
where<i> it</i> started.

17:57.492 --> 18:01.094
The original restaurant
in ocean city, maryland.

18:01.096 --> 18:02.295
How poetic.

18:02.431 --> 18:04.097
The birthplace of shucks

18:04.099 --> 18:06.833
Becomes the deathplace
of shucks.

18:06.969 --> 18:10.137
[ evil laughter ]

18:11.974 --> 18:15.609
There it is!
Yellow nissan rogue!

18:16.911 --> 18:18.779
[ doorbell rings ]

18:18.914 --> 18:20.113
Hello?

18:20.115 --> 18:23.450
Hi, um,
does your son live here?

18:23.452 --> 18:26.719
'cause we've been getting
a mr. Arnold miner's mail

18:26.855 --> 18:28.855
For like 20 years.

18:28.991 --> 18:31.191
[ crying ]

18:31.326 --> 18:34.260
I'm sorry,
arnie was my husband.

18:34.262 --> 18:36.529
He passed
several years ago.

18:36.531 --> 18:38.799
Today is our anniversary.

18:38.934 --> 18:41.334
3d-printed mr. Miner:<i> Tell her</i>
<i> you'd do it all over again</i>

18:41.336 --> 18:44.471
<i> With the perfect</i>
<i> anniversary gift.</i>

18:44.473 --> 18:46.807
Arnie? Is that you?

18:46.942 --> 18:49.942
<i> Every kiss begins with kay.</i>

18:49.944 --> 18:51.611
It<i> is</i> you!

18:51.746 --> 18:56.116
Oh, arnold,
you've returned to me!

18:57.085 --> 18:58.418
Thank you.

18:58.553 --> 19:00.953
Now if you don't mind,
mr. And mrs. Miner

19:00.955 --> 19:04.458
Have several years
of lovemaking to catch up on.

19:05.227 --> 19:06.493
♪ hey ♪

19:06.628 --> 19:09.363
[ laughing, tires screech ]

19:11.900 --> 19:14.401
Destroy...Everything.

19:18.507 --> 19:22.175
I hope these mother[bleep]
have insurance!

19:22.177 --> 19:23.443
Enough with the appetizer.

19:23.578 --> 19:25.978
I'm hungry
for the main course.

19:25.980 --> 19:29.049
Hello, I'd like to order
an entire restaurant

19:29.184 --> 19:30.917
Burned to the ground.

19:31.053 --> 19:33.186
Hahahahahaha!

19:33.321 --> 19:35.188
Drop these babies
in the deep fryer

19:35.190 --> 19:37.724
And your order
will be complete.

19:37.726 --> 19:39.992
The beating heart
of shucks.

19:39.994 --> 19:43.463
And I feel a heart attack
coming on!

19:43.598 --> 19:45.398
Snot, the m-80s,
please.

19:45.400 --> 19:46.667
Snot:
I'm afraid I can't.

19:46.801 --> 19:49.336
We're not really here
to burn down shucks.

19:49.471 --> 19:50.937
We're here
to save you.

19:51.073 --> 19:54.407
The special sauce turned you
into a monster.

19:54.543 --> 19:56.809
That's why
we lured you here.

19:56.811 --> 19:58.945
It's the only place
with enough clams.

19:59.081 --> 20:00.413
Enough clams to what?

20:00.415 --> 20:02.615
To neutralize
the toxic sauce!

20:02.751 --> 20:04.684
I should've known!
[ grunts ]

20:04.819 --> 20:07.487
You still care more
about shucks than me!

20:07.622 --> 20:11.024
We're doing this
<i> because</i> we care about you!

20:11.159 --> 20:14.895
Ghphghphgph!

20:15.029 --> 20:20.767
♪♪

20:20.903 --> 20:26.573
♪♪

20:26.575 --> 20:29.309
Uh.
Ow, my head.

20:29.444 --> 20:30.911
Steve, we're sorry.

20:31.045 --> 20:33.246
If we didn't ditch you
for clams,

20:33.248 --> 20:34.514
This never
would've happened.

20:34.649 --> 20:36.717
And I'm sorry I jeopardized
our friendship

20:36.851 --> 20:38.518
With arson
and light vandalism.

20:38.653 --> 20:40.853
Honestly, after what
we've been through,

20:40.989 --> 20:43.456
I never want to see
another clam again.

20:43.458 --> 20:44.925
As weird as it may sound,

20:45.059 --> 20:46.993
I've kind of developed
a taste for them.

20:47.129 --> 20:48.528
In fact...

20:48.663 --> 20:49.930
Clam me!

20:52.000 --> 20:53.333
Dee-lic--

20:53.468 --> 20:54.768
[ stomach gurgles ]

20:58.006 --> 21:00.207
Bye-bye.
See you soon.
